Files to be compiled into an object must take the form:
FileName.cpp
and be accompanied by a file called:
FileName.hpp
Note that the names must be IDENTICAL.

Code example:
returnType methodName(argType argument)
{
  returnType rv=0; // if necessary
  ObjectType InstanceName;
  if(expression==true)
    singleLineIfStatements(); // are ok
  while(expression) // it's also OK to skip ==true
  {
    // all code blocks with multiple lines should look like this
  }
  switch(X)
  {
    case A:
      doSomething();
      break;
    case B:
    case C:
      doSomethingElse();
      break;
    default:
      // default goes at the bottom
      break;
  }
  return rv; // if necessary
}

I think that should cover more or less everything.

Have fun hacking!
